    <MudExpansionPanel Text="Honey glazed chicken with garlic and chilli">
        <p>4 servings</p>
        <p>Prep: 10m</p>
        <p>Cook: 15m</p>
        <b>Ingredients</b>
        <MudList Dense="true">
             <MudListItem Text="5-6 chicken thighs (boneless)" />
             <MudListItem Text="2tbs cornstarch" />
             <MudListItem Text="1/2 tsp ground pepper" />
             <MudListItem Text="2 tbsp oil" />
             <MudListItem Text="4-5 garlic gloves, minced" />
             <MudListItem Text="1/4 cup chicken stock (0.71ml or 85g) " />
             <MudListItem Text="1/4 cup honey (0.71ml or 85g) Alternatively 106g sugar. (100g sugar = 75g honey)" />
             <MudListItem Text="1 tbsp soy sauce" />
             <MudListItem Text="1 tbsp rice vinegar" />
             <MudListItem Text="1 tsp red chili flakes (2 for a better chance of Filipino approval" />
             <MudListItem Text="1 tbsp parsley, chopped" />
        </MudList>
        <p>Optional: Marinate the thighs in baking soda for 15min - 12hrs. Recommended for chicken breast.</p>
        <b>Steps</b>
        <MudList Dense="true">
             <MudListItem Text="Add chicken thighs to a bowl with cornstarch, salt and pepper. Coat well." />
             <MudListItem Text="In a small bowl: Mix chicken stock, honey, soy sauce, vinegar, chilli flakes and parsley." />
             <MudListItem Text="Heat pan to medium heat. " />
             <MudListItem Text="Add oil to pan. Wait til heated." />
             <MudListItem Text="Add chicken thighs. Cook for 5-6m. Flip when a sear is visible." />
             <MudListItem Text="Move chicken to the sides and add butter to the center." />
             <MudListItem Text="Once melted, add minced garlic and fry for a minute." />
             <MudListItem Text="Add sauce mixture to the pan and cook for 5 minutes on low/medium until sauce has thickened." />
        </MudList>
        <p> Having tapas? This dish can easily be reheated. If the chicken turns out try consider marinating in baking soda. </p>
        <a href="https://gimmedelicious.com/honey-garlic-chicken/">From gimmedelicious.com</a>
